<span style="font-weight: 400;">Â </span><b>Causes Of Gangrene</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Gangrene usually occurs due to lack of blood supply or bacterial infection.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Â When the blood that supplies nutrients and oxygen to feed the tissues fails to do its job, the tissue cells die and start to decay.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Also, if a bacterial infection stays for an extremely long time in the body, it may destroy the tissue cells causing Gangrene.</span>

